CVS ExtraCare Points Expiration Notice

Hey, thanks for sending over those photos from the reunion. I totally forgot we took a group picture by the old oak tree. The one with the sunset in the background came out really well. I was thinking we could make it a yearly thing, maybe rotate who picks the location. I wouldn't mind hosting next summer if the backyard is ready by then. The patio renovation has been dragging on longer than expected, but I think it'll be worth it once we get the fire pit installed. Let me know if you found any other good shots from that day. I'd love to see them before we start planning the next one.

Also, I heard back from the team about the volunteer schedule for next month. They are looking for a few more people to cover the morning shift on Saturdays. I signed up for the first two weekends, but I can switch to afternoons if that helps balance things out. Let me know what works best for you and we can coordinate.

Oh, and I finally picked up that novel you recommended last spring. I'm about halfway through and it is really starting to pick up. The character development is fantastic.

IMPORTANT REMINDER ::: REWARDS EXPIRING SOON

CVS ExtraCare

EXPIRES TOMORROW

Loyalty Points Alert

Your $463.27 balance is set to expire.

Use your ExtraCare rewards before they disappear. Remaining points earned in 2025 must be redeemed by tomorrow to avoid forfeiture.

Rewards Summary

Current Balance

$463.27

Expiration Date

TOMORROW

Points Status

AT RISK

ExtraCare rewards are easy to use. Simply shop at any CVS store or online at CVS.com and apply your balance at checkout.

⏳

DON'T LOSE
YOUR POINTS

Redeem by TOMORROW

Action Required

$463.27 Expiring Tomorrow

If you do not redeem by the deadline, you will forfeit all of your remaining ExtraCare points from 2025. No exceptions can be made once the points expire. Please act now to keep your rewards.

REDEEM YOUR REWARDS

Tap the button to manage your rewards or shop online.

CVS ExtraCare

This is a transactional message regarding your ExtraCare loyalty account. To ensure delivery, add ExtraCare@cvs.com to your address book.

I finally started learning how to play that board game you gifted me last holiday season. It took a couple of reads through the rulebook, but once we got the hang of the resource management phase, it started flowing really nicely. There is a surprising amount of strategy involved for a game that looks so simple on the surface. I can see why you recommended it. We're planning to try out one of the expansion packs this weekend to see how it changes the dynamic.

I'll let you know what we think. Maybe we can schedule a game night soon if you're open to teaching us some of your other favorites. I've been looking for new ways to unwind in the evenings, and this seems like a great fit. Let me know when works for you.

Also, I tried that new coffee shop on the corner of Elm and 5th. Their cold brew is really smooth, and they have a nice outdoor seating area. It might be a good spot to catch up next time.

